LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 349
BY EDUCATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO EDUCATION; AMENDING CHAPTER 5, TITLE 33, IDAHO CODE, BY THE AD-
3 DITION OF A NEW SECTION 33-512E, IDAHO CODE, TO ESTABLISH PROVISIONS
4 REGARDING INAPPROPRIATE ONLINE BEHAVIOR BY STUDENTS AND PRESCRIBING A
5 PROCESS FOR STUDENT DISCIPLINE BY THE SCHOOL DISTRICT OR PUBLIC CHARTER
6 SCHOOL; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
8 SECTION 1. That Chapter 5, Title 33, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
9 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
10 ignated as Section 33-512E, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
11 33-512E. INAPPROPRIATE ONLINE BEHAVIOR -- DISCIPLINARY MEASURES. (1)
12 Any student who engages in inappropriate online behavior as defined in this
13 section toward a public school employee or other person as defined in this
14 section shall be reported to the school district board of trustees or the
15 public charter school governing board for investigation and, if applicable,
16 for imposition of disciplinary measures.
17 (2) For purposes of this section:
18 (a) "Inappropriate online behavior" means any communication through
19 the internet, a mobile electronic device as defined in section
20 49-1401A, Idaho Code, or any other online means, including social me-
21 dia platforms, that harasses, threatens, or bullies any public school
22 employee or other person, whether it occurs during or outside of school
23 hours or on or off school property. The term includes but is not limited
24 to any online communication that:
25 (i) Contains obscene or discriminatory content directed at pub-
26 lic school employees or other persons; or
27 (ii) Harms the reputation, dignity, or safety of public school em-
28 ployees or other persons.
29 (b) "Person" means any student enrolled in any school district or pub-
30 lic charter school, any parent or legal guardian of a student enrolled
31 in any school district or public charter school, or any volunteer at any
32 school district or public charter school.
33 (c) "Public school employee" means a person directly employed by a
34 school district or public charter school, including administrators,
35 instructional staff, and pupil service staff.
36 (3) Upon receipt of a report regarding inappropriate online behavior
37 toward a public school employee or other person, the school district board
38 of trustees or the board's designee or the public charter school governing
39 board or the board's designee shall investigate the matter to determine the
40 veracity of the claims contained in the report. The investigation may in-
41 clude conducting interviews and gathering any relevant evidence. The school
42 district board of trustees or the public charter school governing board

2
1 shall notify the parents or legal guardians of the student about such report
2 and, if appropriate, notify law enforcement.
3 (4) If the school district board of trustees or the public charter
4 school governing board determines that the student engaged in inappropriate
5 online behavior as described in this section, the student and the parents or
6 legal guardians of such student shall meet with the school district board
7 of trustees or the public charter school governing board regarding dis-
8 ciplinary measures. The school district board of trustees or the public
9 charter school governing board shall impose appropriate and proportional
10 disciplinary measures, including but not limited to warning or reprimand,
11 required participation in an online behavior awareness program, temporary
12 suspension, or expulsion.
13 (5) Nothing in this section prohibits or prevents an adversely affected
14 public school employee or other person from pursuing any other available le-
15 gal remedies.
16 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
18 July 1, 2025.

